        'Kong_Vendor_Email_Thread.txt': `═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
EMAIL THREAD - KONG API GATEWAY VULNERABILITY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

From: support@konghq.com
To: platform-team@agency.gov.sg
Date: April 28, 2026 16:45 SGT
Subject: CVE-2024-8912 - Kong Gateway Security Advisory

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Dear Platform Team,

Kong has identified CVE-2024-8912 (CVSS 7.2 HIGH) affecting Kong Gateway
v2.8.x series. This authentication bypass vulnerability requires immediate
attention.

PATCH TIMELINE:
- Kong Gateway v3.4.1 with full patch: August 1, 2026 (60 days)
- Emergency hotfix for v2.8: Not planned (end-of-support version)
- Migration tools for v2.8 → v3.4: July 15, 2026

MIGRATION COMPLEXITY:
Upgrading from Kong 2.8 to 3.4 requires:
1. Kubernetes manifest updates (breaking changes in CRDs)
2. Plugin compatibility verification (5 custom plugins affected)
3. Load testing with full production traffic patterns
4. Blue-green deployment strategy (zero-downtime requirement)
5. Estimated effort: 4-6 weeks engineering time

RECOMMENDED MITIGATION:
Given your off-peak season timing, we recommend risk acceptance with
these compensating controls until August upgrade:

1. AWS WAF rules (we can provide rule templates)
2. Istio service mesh mTLS (already deployed per your config)
3. Kubernetes network policies restricting API Gateway egress
4. Enhanced CloudWatch alerting for suspicious auth patterns
5. Rate limiting at ALB level (before Kong)

EXPLOIT REQUIREMENTS:
- Attacker needs network access to API Gateway public endpoint
- Specific HTTP header manipulation required
- WAF rules block 95% of known exploit variations
- No known public exploits targeting Kubernetes deployments

Kong Security Team will provide weekly threat intelligence updates
during your acceptance period.

Best regards,

Marcus Wong
Senior Security Engineer, Kong Inc.
support@konghq.com

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

From: platform-team@agency.gov.sg
To: support@konghq.com, ciso@agency.gov.sg
Date: April 29, 2026 10:20 SGT
Subject: RE: CVE-2024-8912 - Risk Acceptance Decision

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Marcus / CISO Team,

After reviewing the 60-day patch timeline and our Q2 off-peak season
window, we've decided to proceed with risk acceptance for CVE-2024-8912.

BUSINESS JUSTIFICATION:
1. August upgrade aligns with our scheduled maintenance window
2. Off-peak season (May-July) has 70% reduced traffic
3. Istio mTLS + AWS WAF provide defense-in-depth
4. Zero-downtime requirement prevents emergency patching

We will implement all recommended compensating controls and schedule
the Kong 3.4.1 upgrade for early August.

Platform Engineering Team

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
END OF EMAIL THREAD
